# Naming conventions for Dev::Deps

**Repository subclasses**: `<Thing>Repository` — e.g. `GitRepository`,
`UrlRepository`, `BrewRepository`. Not `Registry`, `Source`, `Adapter`.

**Integration subclasses**: `<Thing>Integration` — e.g. `CmakeIntegration`,
`BrewIntegration`.

**Error classes**: Prefix with the parent class name when the error type is
otherwise generic. Nest inside the class that raises them.

```ruby
# BAD
class InfoError < StandardError; end        # too generic
class DownloadError < StandardError; end    # ambiguous owner

# GOOD (inside BrewRepository)
class BrewInfoError < StandardError; end

# OK when already unambiguous (inside CmakeIntegration)
class GitCloneError < StandardError; end
class GitCheckoutError < StandardError; end
```

**Lockfile constants**: `lock` verb, `read` to get all deps back.
No `write`, no `lockfile_path` params — routing is internal.

**No unnecessary return values**: If a method's job is a side effect (install,
write), don't `return true`. Let it return nil implicitly.
